 0592:     r'''
 0593:     extern "C" __global__
 0594:     
 0595:     void bpf_kernel1(unsigned char * current, unsigned char * previous,
 0596:         const int w, const int h, const double threshold)
 0597:     {
 0598:         int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 0599:         int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 0600: 
 0601:         const int t_max  = w * h;    
 0602:         const int index  = j * h + i;
 0603:         const int index1 = j * h * 3 + i * 3;
 0604: 
 0605:         __syncthreads();
 0606: 
 0607:         if (index > 0 && index < t_max){            
 0608: 
 0609:             float r  = (float)previous[index1    ];
 0610:             float g  = (float)previous[index1 + 1];
 0611:             float b  = (float)previous[index1 + 2];
 0612: 
 0613:              // ITU-R BT.601 luma coefficients
 0614:             float lum = r * 0.299f + g * 0.587f + b * 0.114f;    
 0615:             if (lum > threshold) {
 0616:                 float c = (float)((lum - threshold) / (lum +1));
 0617:                 current[index1    ] = (unsigned char)(r * c);
 0618:                 current[index1 + 1] = (unsigned char)(g * c);
 0619:                 current[index1 + 2] = (unsigned char)(b * c);   
 0620:             } 
 0621:              else {
 0622:                 current[index1    ] = (unsigned char)0;
 0623:                 current[index1 + 1] = (unsigned char)0;
 0624:                 current[index1 + 2] = (unsigned char)0;                    
 0625:             }
 0626: 
 0627:             __syncthreads();
 0628: 
 0629:         }
 0630:     }
 0631:     ''',

 1070:     '''

 1074:     __constant__ double gy[9] = {1.0, 0.0, -1.0, 2.0, 0.0, -2.0, 1.0, 0.0, -1.0};

 1077:                      double* return_value)

 1081:     double magnitude=0;

 1148:     '''
 1149:     
 1150:     extern "C" 
 1151:     
 1152:     __constant__ double kernel[5][5] = 
 1153:         {{2.0, 4.0,  5.0,  4.0,  2.0}, 
 1154:          {4.0, 9.0,  12.0, 9.0,  4.0}, 
 1155:          {5.0, 12.0, 15.0, 12.0, 5.0}, 
 1156:          {4.0, 9.0,  12.0, 9.0,  4.0}, 
 1157:          {2.0, 4.0,  5.0,  4.0,  2.0}};
 1158:     
 1159:     __global__ void canny_smooth(double* buffer, int filter_size,
 1160:                      double* return_value)
 1161:     {
 1162:     double color=0;
 1163:     
 1164:   
 1165:     for (int i=0; i<filter_size; ++i){
 1166:         for (int kx = 0; kx < 4; ++kx){
 1167:             for (int ky = 0; ky < 4; ++ky){
 1168:                 color += buffer[i] * kernel[kx][ky]/159.0;
 1169:     
 1170:             }
 1171:         }
 1172:     }
 1173:     color /= 25.0;
 1174:     if (color > 255.0f) {color = 255.0f;} 
 1175:     else if (color < 0.0f) {color = 0.0;}   
 1176:        
 1177:     return_value[0] = color;
 1178:     }

+1506: rgb2hsv_cuda = r'''   
  if (PyDict_SetItem(__pyx_d, __pyx_n_s_rgb2hsv_cuda, __pyx_kp_u_extern_C___global___void_rgb2hs) < 0) __PYX_ERR(0, 1506, __pyx_L1_error)

 1507:     extern "C"
 1508:     
 1509:     __global__ void rgb2hsv(float * r, float * g, float * b, int width, int height, double val_)
 1510:     {
 1511:     
 1512:     int xx = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;     
 1513:     int yy = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 1514:     
 1515:     // Index value of the current pixel
 1516:     const int index = yy * height + xx;
 1517:     const int t_max = height * width;
 1518:      
 1519:     if (index> 0 && index < t_max){ 
 1520:      
 1521:     float h, s, v;
 1522:     int i=-1; 
 1523:     float f, p, q, t;
 1524:     float mx, mn;
 1525:     
 1526:     // Create a reference to RGB
 1527:     float rr = r[index];
 1528:     float gg = g[index];
 1529:     float bb = b[index];
 1530:     
 1531:     // Find max and min of RGB values 
 1532:     if (rr > gg){
 1533: 		if (rr > bb){
 1534: 			mx = rr;
 1535: 			if (bb > gg){ mn = gg;}
 1536: 			else mn = bb;
 1537:         }
 1538: 		else{
 1539: 			mx = bb;
 1540: 			if (bb > gg){ mn = gg;}
 1541: 			else mn = bb;
 1542: 		}
 1543:     }
 1544: 	else{
 1545: 		if (gg > bb){
 1546: 			mx = gg;
 1547: 			if (bb > rr){ mn = rr;}
 1548: 			else mn = bb;
 1549: 		} 
 1550: 		else{
 1551: 			mx = bb;
 1552: 			if (bb > rr) { mn = rr;}
 1553: 			else  mn = bb;
 1554: 		}
 1555:     }
 1556:     
 1557:     
 1558:     __syncthreads();
 1559:     
 1560:     // Convert RGB to HSV 
 1561:     float df = mx-mn;  
 1562:     float df_ = 1.0f/df;        
 1563:        
 1564:     if (mx == mn)
 1565:     { h = 0.0;}
 1566:   
 1567:     else if (mx == rr){
 1568: 	    h = (float)fmod(60.0f * ((gg-bb) * df_) + 360.0, 360);
 1569: 	}
 1570:     else if (mx == gg){
 1571: 	    h = (float)fmod(60.0f * ((bb-rr) * df_) + 120.0, 360);
 1572: 	}
 1573:     else if (mx == bb){
 1574: 	    h = (float)fmod(60.0f * ((rr-gg) * df_) + 240.0, 360);
 1575:     }
 1576:     
 1577:     if (mx == 0.0){
 1578:         s = 0.0;
 1579:     }
 1580:     else{
 1581:         s = df/mx;
 1582:     }
 1583:      
 1584:     v = mx;   
 1585:     h = h * 1.0f/360.0f;
 1586: 
 1587:     // Increment the hue 
 1588:     h = (float)fmod(h + val_, (double)1.0);
 1589: 
 1590:     __syncthreads();
 1591:     
 1592:     // Convert HSV to RGB    
 1593:     if (s == 0.0){
 1594:          r[index] = v;
 1595:          g[index] = v;
 1596:          b[index] = v;         
 1597:          }
 1598:     else {
 1599:         i = (int)(h*6.0f);
 1600:         f = (h*6.0f) - i;
 1601:         p = v*(1.0f - s);
 1602:         q = v*(1.0f - s*f);
 1603:         t = v*(1.0f - s*(1.0f-f));
 1604:         i = i%6;
 1605:         
 1606:         switch(i) { 
 1607:             case 0:
 1608:                 r[index] = v;
 1609:                 g[index] = t;
 1610:                 b[index] = p;
 1611:                 break; 
 1612:             case 1: 
 1613:                 r[index] = q; 
 1614:                 g[index] = v;
 1615:                 b[index] = p;
 1616:                 break;
 1617:             case 2:
 1618:                 r[index] = p;
 1619:                 g[index] = v;
 1620:                 b[index] = t;
 1621:                 break;
 1622:             case 3:
 1623:                 r[index] = p;
 1624:                 g[index] = q;
 1625:                 b[index] = v;
 1626:                 break;
 1627:             case 4:
 1628:                 r[index] = t;
 1629:                 g[index] = p;
 1630:                 b[index] = v;
 1631:                 break;
 1632:             case 5: 
 1633:                 r[index] = v;
 1634:                 g[index] = p; 
 1635:                 b[index] = q;
 1636:                 break;
 1637:             default:
 1638:                 ;
 1639:

 2522:     """
 2523:     BLEND A SOURCE TEXTURE TOWARD A DESTINATION TEXTURE (TRANSITION EFFECT)
 2524: 
 2525:     * Video system must be initialised 
 2526:     * source_ & destination_ Textures must be same sizes
 2527:     * Compatible with 24 - 32 bit surface
 2528:     * Output create a new surface
 2529:     * Image returned is converted for fast blit (convert())
 2530: 
 2531:     # ***********************************
 2532:     # Calculations for alpha & RGB values
 2533:     # outA = SrcA + DstA(1 - SrcA)
 2534:     # outRGB = SrcRGB + DstRGB(1 - SrcA)

 2536:

 2538:     :param destination_: pygame.Surface (Destination)

 2670:     r'''
 2671:     extern "C" __global__
 2672:     void ripple_kernel(float * current, float * previous, 
 2673:     unsigned char * background_array, unsigned char * texture_array,    
 2674:     const int w, const int h)
 2675:     {
 2676:         int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 2677:         int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 2678:         
 2679:         // index for array shape (w, h)
 2680:         const int index = j * h + i;
 2681:         
 2682:         // index for array shape (w, h, 3) e.g texture & background 
 2683:         const int index1 = j * h * 3 + i * 3;
 2684:         
 2685:         // Maximum index value for array shape (w, h) 
 2686:         const int t_max = w * h;
 2687:         
 2688:         // Maximum index value for array shape (w, h, 3
 2689:         const int t_max_ = w * h * 3;
 2690:         
 2691:         __syncthreads();
 2692:         
 2693:         float left = 0.0f;
 2694:         float right = 0.0f; 
 2695:         float top = 0.0f; 
 2696:         float bottom = 0.0f;
 2697:         float data = 0.0f;
 2698:         
 2699:         // Limit the loop to the valid indexes 
 2700:         if (index> 0 && index < t_max){
 2701:             
 2702:             /*
 2703:             float data = (previous[max((index + 1) % t_max, 0)] +                 // left  
 2704:                           previous[max((index - 1) % t_max, 0)] +                 // right 
 2705:                           previous[max((index - h) % t_max, 0)] +                 // top 
 2706:                           previous[max((index + h) % t_max, 0)]) * (float)0.5;    // bottom
 2707:             */
 2708:             
 2709:             
 2710:             
 2711:             if ((index - h) < 0) {
 2712:                 top = 0.0f;
 2713:             }
 2714:             else {
 2715:                 top = previous[index - h];
 2716:             }
 2717:             
 2718:             if ((index + h) > t_max) {
 2719:                 bottom = 0.0f; 
 2720:             } 
 2721:               else {
 2722:                 bottom = previous[index + h];
 2723:             }
 2724:             
 2725:             
 2726:             if ((index - 1) < 0) {
 2727:                 right = 0.0f;
 2728:             }
 2729:             else {
 2730:                 right = previous[index - 1];
 2731:             }
 2732:             
 2733:             if ((index + 1) > t_max) {
 2734:                 left = 0.0f;
 2735:             } 
 2736:             else {
 2737:                 left = previous[index + 1];
 2738:             }
 2739:             
 2740:             
 2741:             data = (left + right + top + bottom) * 0.5f; 
 2742:             
 2743:             
 2744:               
 2745:             data = data - current[index];
 2746:             data = data - (data * 0.01125f);   // Attenuation
 2747:              
 2748:             __syncthreads();
 2749:             
 2750:             current[index] = data;
 2751:             
 2752:                 
 2753:             data = 1.0f - data * 1.0f/1024.0f;
 2754:             const int w2 = w >> 1;
 2755:             const int h2 = h >> 1;
 2756:             const int a = max((int)(((i - w2) * data) + w2) % h, 0);              // texture index (x)
 2757:             const int b = max((int)(((j - h2) * data) + h2) % w, 0);              // texture index (y)
 2758:             // int ind = a * h * 3 + b * 3;   // inverse texture
 2759:             const int ind = b * h * 3 + a * 3;
 2760:             background_array[index1       ] = texture_array[ind       ];    // red
 2761:             background_array[(index1 + 1) ] = texture_array[(ind + 1) ];    // green 
 2762:             background_array[(index1 + 2) ] = texture_array[(ind + 2) ];    // blue
 2763:             
 2764:             __syncthreads();
 2765:         }
 2766:     }
 2767:     ''',
 2768:     'ripple_kernel'
 2769: )

 2790:     This method call cuda kernel ripple_kernel to do the math with the GPU

 2792:

 2819:     r'''
 2820:     extern "C" __global__
 2821:     void sharpen1_kernel(float * current, float * previous, 
 2822:     const int w, const int h)
 2823:     {
 2824:         int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 2825:         int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 2826: 
 2827:         const int col = h * 3;
 2828: 
 2829:         // index for array shape (w, h)
 2830:         const int index = j * h + i;
 2831: 
 2832:         // index for array shape (w, h, 3) e.g texture & background 
 2833:         const int index1 = j * col + i * 3;
 2834: 
 2835:         // Maximum index value for array shape (w, h) 
 2836:         const int t_max = w * h;
 2837: 
 2838:         // Maximum index value for array shape (w, h, 3
 2839:         const int t_max_ = w * col;
 2840:         
 2841:         
 2842:         __syncthreads();
 2843:         
 2844:         float red   = 0;
 2845:         float green = 0;
 2846:         float blue  = 0;
 2847: 
 2848:         // Limit the loop to the valid indexes 
 2849:         if (index > 0 && index < t_max){
 2850:             
 2851:             if ((index1 - col> 0) && (index1 + col < t_max_)) {
 2852:             
 2853:             red = 
 2854:                         -previous[index1 - col          ] +                               
 2855:                         -previous[index1 - 3            ] +          
 2856:                          previous[index1                ] * 5.0f  +          
 2857:                         -previous[index1 + 3            ] +                           
 2858:                         -previous[index1 + col          ];          
 2859:                          
 2860:             green =  
 2861:                         -previous[index1 - col  + 1     ] +                                 
 2862:                         -previous[index1 - 2            ] +         
 2863:                          previous[index1 + 1            ] * 5.0f  +          
 2864:                         -previous[index1 + 4            ] +                           
 2865:                         -previous[index1 + col + 1      ];        
 2866:                                              
 2867:             blue =         
 2868:                         -previous[index1 - col + 2     ] +                                  
 2869:                         -previous[index1 - 1           ] +          
 2870:                          previous[index1 + 2           ] * 5.0f  +          
 2871:                         -previous[index1 + 5           ] +                         
 2872:                         -previous[index1 + col + 2     ];                     
 2873:             }
 2874:             
 2875:             __syncthreads();     
 2876:                        
 2877:             if (red > 255) { red = 255; } 
 2878:             if (red < 0) { red = 0; }
 2879:             
 2880:             if (green > 255) { green = 255; } 
 2881:             if (green < 0) { green = 0; }
 2882:             
 2883:             if (blue > 255) { blue = 255; } 
 2884:             if (blue < 0) { blue = 0; }
 2885:                   
 2886:             current[ index1     ] = red;
 2887:             current[ index1 + 1 ] = green;
 2888:             current[ index1 + 2 ] = blue;
 2889:             
 2890:             
 2891:             __syncthreads();
 2892:             
 2893:         }
 2894:     }

 3003:     r'''
 3004:     extern "C" __global__
 3005:     void mirror_kernel(float * current, float * previous, 
 3006:     const int w, const int h, bool format)
 3007:     {
 3008:         int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 3009:         int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 3010: 
 3011:         const int col = h * 3;
 3012: 
 3013:         // index for array shape (w, h)
 3014:         const int index = j * h + i;
 3015: 
 3016:         // index for array shape (w, h, 3) e.g texture & background 
 3017:         const int index1 = j * col + i * 3;
 3018: 
 3019:         // Maximum index value for array shape (w, h) 
 3020:         const int t_max = w * h;
 3021: 
 3022:         // Maximum index value for array shape (w, h, 3)
 3023:         const int t_max_ = w * col;
 3024: 
 3025:         __syncthreads();
 3026: 
 3027:         float red   = 0;
 3028:         float green = 0;
 3029:         float blue  = 0;
 3030:         int x2, x3;
 3031: 
 3032:         // Limit the loop to the valid indexes 
 3033:         if (index > 0 && index < t_max){
 3034: 
 3035:             red   = previous[index1    ];       
 3036:             green = previous[index1 + 1];
 3037:             blue  = previous[index1 + 2];     
 3038: 
 3039:             __syncthreads(); 
 3040: 
 3041:             if (format == 1){
 3042: 
 3043:             x2 = i >> 1;
 3044: 
 3045:             current[j * col + x2 * 3    ] = red;
 3046:             current[j * col + x2 * 3 + 1] = green;
 3047:             current[j * col + x2 * 3 + 2] = blue;
 3048:             __syncthreads(); 
 3049: 
 3050:             x3 = h - x2 - 1;
 3051: 
 3052:             current[j * col + x3 * 3    ] = red;
 3053:             current[j * col + x3 * 3 + 1] = green;
 3054:             current[j * col + x3 * 3 + 2] = blue;
 3055:             }
 3056:             else{
 3057: 
 3058:             x2 = j >> 1;
 3059: 
 3060:             current[x2 * h * 3 + i * 3    ] = red;
 3061:             current[x2 * h * 3 + i * 3 + 1] = green;
 3062:             current[x2 * h * 3 + i * 3 + 2] = blue;
 3063: 
 3064:             __syncthreads();   
 3065: 
 3066:             x3 = w - x2 - 1;
 3067: 
 3068:             current[x3 * h * 3 + i * 3    ] = red;
 3069:             current[x3 * h * 3 + i * 3 + 1] = green;
 3070:             current[x3 * h * 3 + i * 3 + 2] = blue;
 3071:             }
 3072: 
 3073:             __syncthreads();     
 3074: 
 3075:         }
 3076:     }

 3167:     extern "C" __global__

 3169:     {
 3170:         int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 3171:         int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;

 3175:         const int t_max  = width * height;
 3176:         
 3177:         float h, s, v;
 3178:         int ii = 0; 
 3179:         float f, p, q, t;
 3180:         float mx, mn;
 3181:

 3183:         
 3184:         float red   = 0.0f;
 3185:         float green = 0.0f;
 3186:         float blue  = 0.0f;
 3187: 
 3188:         if (index > 0 && index < t_max) {
 3189:        
 3190: 
 3191:         red   = source[index1    ] / 255.0f;       
 3192:         green = source[index1 + 1] / 255.0f;
 3193:         blue  = source[index1 + 2] / 255.0f;    
 3194:         
 3195:         
 3196:     
 3197:         // Find max and min of RGB values 
 3198:         if (red > green){
 3199:             if (red > blue){
 3200:                 mx = red;
 3201:                 if (blue > green){ mn = green;}
 3202:                 else mn = blue;
 3203:             }
 3204:             else{
 3205:                 mx = blue;
 3206:                 if (blue > green){ mn = green;}
 3207:                 else mn = blue;
 3208:             }
 3209:         }
 3210:         else{
 3211:             if (green > blue){
 3212:                 mx = green;
 3213:                 if (blue > red){ mn = red;}
 3214:                 else mn = blue;
 3215:             } 
 3216:             else{
 3217:                 mx = blue;
 3218:                 if (blue > red) { mn = red;}
 3219:                 else  mn = blue;
 3220:             }
 3221:         }  
 3222:             
 3223:             
 3224:         // Convert RGB to HSV 
 3225:         float df = mx-mn;  
 3226:         float df_ = 1.0f/df;        
 3227:     
 3228:         if (mx == mn)
 3229:         { h = 0.0;}
 3230:     
 3231:         else if (mx == red){
 3232:             h = (float)fmod(60.0f * ((green-blue) * df_) + 360.0, 360);
 3233:         }
 3234:         else if (mx == green){
 3235:             h = (float)fmod(60.0f * ((blue-red) * df_) + 120.0, 360);
 3236:         }
 3237:         else if (mx == blue){
 3238:             h = (float)fmod(60.0f * ((red-green) * df_) + 240.0, 360);
 3239:         }
 3240:     
 3241:         if (mx == 0.0){
 3242:             s = 0.0;
 3243:         }
 3244:         else{
 3245:             s = df/mx;
 3246:         }

 3257:

It replaces the intensity of each pixel with a\n    weighted average of intensity values from nearby pixels. This weight can be\n    based on a Gaussian distribution.\n\n    sigma_r & sigma_s are hard encoded in the GPU kernel\n    Compatible with 32 - 24 bit image \n\n    :param surface_     : pygame.Surface \n    :param kernel_size_ : int; Kernel size (or neighbours pixels to be included in the calculation) \n    :return             : Return a 24 bit pygame.Surface with bilateral effect\n    ";

 3371:     smoothing filter for images. It replaces the intensity of each pixel with a
 3372:     weighted average of intensity values from nearby pixels. This weight can be
 3373:     based on a Gaussian distribution.
 3374: 
 3375:     sigma_r & sigma_s are hard encoded in the GPU kernel
 3376:     Compatible with 32 - 24 bit image 
 3377: 
 3378:     :param surface_     : pygame.Surface 
 3379:     :param kernel_size_ : int; Kernel size (or neighbours pixels to be included in the calculation) 
 3380:     :return             : Return a 24 bit pygame.Surface with bilateral effect
 3381:     """

 3405:     '''
 3406:     extern "C" __global__
 3407:     void bilateral_kernel(double* source, int filter_size, double* destination)
 3408:     {
 3409: 
 3410:     // float sigma_i (also call sigma_r) range kernel, 
 3411:     // minimum amplitude of an edge.
 3412:     const double sigma_i2 = 80 * 80 * 2;   
 3413:     // float sigma_s : Spatial extent of the kernel, size of the 
 3414:     // considered neighborhood
 3415:     const double sigma_s2 = 16 * 16 * 2;  
 3416: 
 3417:     double ir = 0.0; 
 3418:     double wpr = 0.0;  
 3419:     double r=0.0, dist=0.0, gs=0.0;  
 3420:     double vr=0.0, wr=0.0;  
 3421:     const double p = 3.14159265;
 3422:     const int k2 = (int)sqrt((float)filter_size);
 3423: 
 3424:     int a = 0;
 3425: 
 3426:     __syncthreads();
 3427: 
 3428:     for (int ky = 0; ky < k2; ++ky)
 3429:     {
 3430:         for (int kx = 0; kx < k2; ++kx)
 3431:         {    
 3432: 
 3433:             dist = (double)sqrt((double)kx * (double)kx + (double)ky * (double)ky);
 3434:             gs = ((double)1.0 / (p * sigma_s2)) * (double)exp(-(dist * dist ) / sigma_s2);             
 3435:             r = source[a];
 3436:             vr = r - source[filter_size >> 1];
 3437:             wr = ((double)1.0 / (p * sigma_i2)) * (double)exp(-(vr * vr ) / sigma_i2);
 3438:             wr = wr *  gs;
 3439: 
 3440:             ir = ir + r * wr;          
 3441:             wpr = wpr + wr;
 3442:             a += 1;
 3443: 
 3444:         } // for
 3445:     } // for
 3446: 
 3447:     __syncthreads();
 3448: 
 3449:     ir = ir / wpr;
 3450:     if (ir > 255.0) {ir = 255.0;}
 3451:     if (ir < 0.0) {ir = 0.0;} 
 3452:     destination[0] = ir;
 3453: 
 3454:     __syncthreads();
 3455: 
 3456:     } //main
 3457: 
 3458:     ''',
 3459:     'bilateral_kernel'
 3460: )
 3461: 
 3462: @cython.boundscheck(False)
 3463: @cython.wraparound(False)
 3464: @cython.nonecheck(False)
 3465: @cython.cdivision(True)
 3466: @cython.profile(False)

  if (PyDict_SetItem(__pyx_d, __pyx_n_s_brightness_cuda, __pyx_kp_u_struct_hsl_float_h_hue_float_s) < 0) __PYX_ERR(0, 3745, __pyx_L1_error)

 3748:     struct hsl{
 3749:         float h;    // hue
 3750:         float s;    // saturation
 3751:         float l;    // value
 3752:     };
 3753:     
 3754:     struct rgb{
 3755:     float r;
 3756:     float g;
 3757:     float b;
 3758:     };
 3759:     
 3760:     __device__ struct rgb struct_hsl_to_rgb(float h, float s, float l);
 3761:     __device__ struct hsl struct_rgb_to_hsl(float r, float g, float b);
 3762:     __device__ float hue_to_rgb(float m1, float m2, float h);
 3763:     __device__ float fmin_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue);
 3764:     __device__ float fmax_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue);
 3765:   
 3766:   
 3767:     
 3768:     
 3769:     
 3770:     __device__ float fmax_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue)
 3771:     {
 3772:         if (red>green){
 3773:             if (red>blue) {
 3774:                 return red;
 3775:         }
 3776:             else {
 3777:                 return blue;
 3778:             }
 3779:         }
 3780:         else if (green>blue){
 3781:             return green;
 3782:         }
 3783:         else {
 3784:             return blue;
 3785:         }
 3786:     }
 3787:     
 3788: 
 3789:     __device__ float fmin_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue)
 3790:     {
 3791:         if (red<green){
 3792:             if (red<blue){
 3793:                 return red;
 3794:             }
 3795:         else{
 3796:             return blue;}
 3797:         }
 3798:         else if (green<blue){
 3799:             return green;
 3800:         }
 3801:         else{
 3802:             return blue;
 3803:         }
 3804:     }
 3805:     
 3806:     
 3807:     __device__ float hue_to_rgb(float m1, float m2, float h)
 3808:         {
 3809:             if ((fabs(h) > 1.0f) && (h > 0.0f)) {
 3810:               h = (float)fmod(h, 1.0f);
 3811:             }
 3812:             else if (h < 0.0f){
 3813:             h = 1.0f - (float)fabs(h);
 3814:             }
 3815:         
 3816:             if (h < 1.0f/6.0f){
 3817:                 return m1 + (m2 - m1) * h * 6.0f;
 3818:             }
 3819:             if (h < 0.5f){
 3820:                 return m2;
 3821:             }
 3822:             if (h < 2.0f/3.0f){
 3823:                 return m1 + ( m2 - m1 ) * (float)((float)2.0f/3.0f - h) * 6.0f;
 3824:             }
 3825:             return m1;
 3826:         }
 3827:     
 3828:     __device__ struct hsl struct_rgb_to_hsl(float r, float g, float b)
 3829:     {
 3830:     // check if all inputs are normalized
 3831:     assert ((0.0<= r) <= 1.0);
 3832:     assert ((0.0<= g) <= 1.0);
 3833:     assert ((0.0<= b) <= 1.0);
 3834: 
 3835:     struct hsl hsl_;
 3836: 
 3837:     float cmax=0.0f, cmin=0.0f, delta=0.0f, t;
 3838: 
 3839:     cmax = fmax_rgb_value(r, g, b);
 3840:     cmin = fmin_rgb_value(r, g, b);
 3841:     delta = (cmax - cmin);
 3842: 
 3843: 
 3844:     float h, l, s;
 3845:     l = (cmax + cmin) / 2.0f;
 3846: 
 3847:     if (delta == 0) {
 3848:     h = 0.0f;
 3849:     s = 0.0f;
 3850:     }
 3851:     else {
 3852:     	  if (cmax == r){
 3853:     	        t = (g - b) / delta;
 3854:     	        if ((fabs(t) > 6.0f) && (t > 0.0f)) {
 3855:                   t = (float)fmod(t, 6.0f);
 3856:                 }
 3857:                 else if (t < 0.0f){
 3858:                 t = 6.0f - (float)fabs(t);
 3859:                 }
 3860: 
 3861: 	            h = 60.0f * t;
 3862:           }
 3863:     	  else if (cmax == g){
 3864:                 h = 60.0f * (((b - r) / delta) + 2.0f);
 3865:           }
 3866: 
 3867:     	  else if (cmax == b){
 3868:     	        h = 60.0f * (((r - g) / delta) + 4.0f);
 3869:           }
 3870: 
 3871:     	  if (l <=0.5f) {
 3872: 	            s=(delta/(cmax + cmin));
 3873: 	      }
 3874: 	  else {
 3875: 	        s=(delta/(2.0f - cmax - cmin));
 3876: 	  }
 3877:     }
 3878: 
 3879:     hsl_.h = (float)(h * (float)1.0f/360.0f);
 3880:     hsl_.s = s;
 3881:     hsl_.l = l;
 3882:     return hsl_;
 3883:     }
 3884: 
 3885:     
 3886:     
 3887:     __device__ struct rgb struct_hsl_to_rgb(float h, float s, float l)
 3888:     {
 3889:     
 3890:         struct rgb rgb_;
 3891:     
 3892:         float m2=0.0f, m1=0.0f;
 3893:     
 3894:         if (s == 0.0){
 3895:             rgb_.r = l;
 3896:             rgb_.g = l;
 3897:             rgb_.b = l;
 3898:             return rgb_;
 3899:         }
 3900:         if (l <= 0.5f){
 3901:             m2 = l * (1.0f + s);
 3902:         }
 3903:         else{
 3904:             m2 = l + s - (l * s);
 3905:         }
 3906:         m1 = 2.0f * l - m2;
 3907:     
 3908:         rgb_.r = hue_to_rgb(m1, m2, (float)(h + 1.0f/3.0f));
 3909:         rgb_.g = hue_to_rgb(m1, m2, h);
 3910:         rgb_.b = hue_to_rgb(m1, m2, (float)(h - 1.0f/3.0f));
 3911:         return rgb_;
 3912:     }
 3913:     
 3914:     extern "C"  __global__ void brightness(float * r, float * g, float * b, int width, int height, double val_)
 3915:     { 
 3916:         int xx = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;     
 3917:         int yy = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 3918:     
 3919:         // Index value of the current pixel
 3920:         const int index = yy * height + xx;
 3921:         const int t_max = height * width;
 3922:        
 3923:         struct hsl hsl_; 
 3924:         struct rgb rgb_;
 3925:         
 3926:         if (index > 0 && index < t_max) { 
 3927:             
 3928:             float rr = r[index] ;
 3929:             float gg = g[index] ;
 3930:             float bb = b[index] ;
 3931:             
 3932:             hsl_ = struct_rgb_to_hsl(rr, gg, bb);
 3933:             hsl_.l += val_;
 3934:             hsl_.l = max(hsl_.l, -1.0f);
 3935:             hsl_.l = min(hsl_.l, 1.0f);
 3936:             rgb_ = struct_hsl_to_rgb(hsl_.h, hsl_.s, hsl_.l); 
 3937:             
 3938:             r[index] = rgb_.r ;
 3939:             g[index] = rgb_.g ;
 3940:             b[index] = rgb_.b ;
 3941:             
 3942:         } 
 3943:         
 3944:         
 3945:     }

 4071: 
 4072:     __device__ struct rgb struct_hsl_to_rgb(float h, float s, float l);
 4073:     __device__ struct hsl struct_rgb_to_hsl(float r, float g, float b);
 4074:     __device__ float hue_to_rgb(float m1, float m2, float h);
 4075:     __device__ float fmin_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue);
 4076:     __device__ float fmax_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue);
 4077: 
 4078:     __device__ float fmax_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue)
 4079:     {
 4080:         if (red>green){
 4081:             if (red>blue) {
 4082:                 return red;
 4083:         }
 4084:             else {
 4085:                 return blue;
 4086:             }
 4087:         }
 4088:         else if (green>blue){
 4089:             return green;
 4090:         }
 4091:         else {
 4092:             return blue;
 4093:         }
 4094:     }
 4095: 
 4096:     __device__ float fmin_rgb_value(float red, float green, float blue)
 4097:     {
 4098:         if (red<green){
 4099:             if (red<blue){
 4100:                 return red;
 4101:             }
 4102:         else{
 4103:             return blue;}
 4104:         }
 4105:         else if (green<blue){
 4106:             return green;
 4107:         }
 4108:         else{
 4109:             return blue;
 4110:         }
 4111:     }
 4112: 
 4113:     __device__ float hue_to_rgb(float m1, float m2, float h)
 4114:         {
 4115:             if ((fabs(h) > 1.0f) && (h > 0.0f)) {
 4116:               h = (float)fmod(h, 1.0f);
 4117:             }
 4118:             else if (h < 0.0f){
 4119:             h = 1.0f - (float)fabs(h);
 4120:             }
 4121: 
 4122:             if (h < 1.0f/6.0f){
 4123:                 return m1 + (m2 - m1) * h * 6.0f;
 4124:             }
 4125:             if (h < 0.5f){
 4126:                 return m2;
 4127:             }
 4128:             if (h < 2.0f/3.0f){
 4129:                 return m1 + ( m2 - m1 ) * (float)((float)2.0f/3.0f - h) * 6.0f;
 4130:             }
 4131:             return m1;
 4132:         }
 4133: 
 4134:     __device__ struct hsl struct_rgb_to_hsl(float r, float g, float b)
 4135:     {
 4136:     // check if all inputs are normalized
 4137:     assert ((0.0<= r) <= 1.0);
 4138:     assert ((0.0<= g) <= 1.0);
 4139:     assert ((0.0<= b) <= 1.0);
 4140: 
 4141:     struct hsl hsl_;
 4142: 
 4143:     float cmax=0.0f, cmin=0.0f, delta=0.0f, t;
 4144: 
 4145:     cmax = fmax_rgb_value(r, g, b);
 4146:     cmin = fmin_rgb_value(r, g, b);
 4147:     delta = (cmax - cmin);
 4148: 
 4149: 
 4150:     float h, l, s;
 4151:     l = (cmax + cmin) / 2.0f;
 4152: 
 4153:     if (delta == 0) {
 4154:     h = 0.0f;
 4155:     s = 0.0f;
 4156:     }
 4157:     else {
 4158:     	  if (cmax == r){
 4159:     	        t = (g - b) / delta;
 4160:     	        if ((fabs(t) > 6.0f) && (t > 0.0f)) {
 4161:                   t = (float)fmod(t, 6.0f);
 4162:                 }
 4163:                 else if (t < 0.0f){
 4164:                 t = 6.0f - (float)fabs(t);
 4165:                 }
 4166: 
 4167: 	            h = 60.0f * t;
 4168:           }
 4169:     	  else if (cmax == g){
 4170:                 h = 60.0f * (((b - r) / delta) + 2.0f);
 4171:           }
 4172: 
 4173:     	  else if (cmax == b){
 4174:     	        h = 60.0f * (((r - g) / delta) + 4.0f);
 4175:           }
 4176: 
 4177:     	  if (l <=0.5f) {
 4178: 	            s=(delta/(cmax + cmin));
 4179: 	      }
 4180: 	  else {
 4181: 	        s=(delta/(2.0f - cmax - cmin));
 4182: 	  }
 4183:     }
 4184: 
 4185:     hsl_.h = (float)(h * (float)1.0f/360.0f);
 4186:     hsl_.s = s;
 4187:     hsl_.l = l;
 4188:     return hsl_;
 4189:     }
 4190: 
 4191: 
 4192: 
 4193:     __device__ struct rgb struct_hsl_to_rgb(float h, float s, float l)
 4194:     {
 4195: 
 4196:         struct rgb rgb_;
 4197: 
 4198:         float m2=0.0f, m1=0.0f;
 4199: 
 4200:         if (s == 0.0){
 4201:             rgb_.r = l;
 4202:             rgb_.g = l;
 4203:             rgb_.b = l;
 4204:             return rgb_;
 4205:         }
 4206:         if (l <= 0.5f){
 4207:             m2 = l * (1.0f + s);
 4208:         }
 4209:         else{
 4210:             m2 = l + s - (l * s);
 4211:         }
 4212:         m1 = 2.0f * l - m2;
 4213: 
 4214:         rgb_.r = hue_to_rgb(m1, m2, (float)(h + 1.0f/3.0f));
 4215:         rgb_.g = hue_to_rgb(m1, m2, h);
 4216:         rgb_.b = hue_to_rgb(m1, m2, (float)(h - 1.0f/3.0f));
 4217:         return rgb_;
 4218:     }
 4219: 
 4220:     extern "C"  __global__ void rgb2hsl(float * r, float * g, float * b, int width, int height, double val_)
 4221:     { 
 4222:         int xx = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;     
 4223:         int yy = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 4224: 
 4225:         // Index value of the current pixel
 4226:         const int index = yy * height + xx;
 4227:         const int t_max = height * width;
 4228: 
 4229:         struct hsl hsl_; 
 4230:         struct rgb rgb_;
 4231:         float h; 
 4232:         if (index > 0 && index < t_max) { 
 4233: 
 4234:             float rr = r[index] ;
 4235:             float gg = g[index] ;
 4236:             float bb = b[index] ;
 4237: 
 4238:             hsl_ = struct_rgb_to_hsl(rr, gg, bb);
 4239:             h += hsl_.h + val_;
 4240:             rgb_ = struct_hsl_to_rgb(h, hsl_.s, hsl_.l); 
 4241: 
 4242:             r[index] = rgb_.r ;
 4243:             g[index] = rgb_.g ;
 4244:             b[index] = rgb_.b ;
 4245:         } 
 4246:     }

 4438:     r'''
 4439:     
 4440:     extern "C" __global__
 4441:     
 4442:     void fisheye_kernel(unsigned char * destination, unsigned char * source,    
 4443:     const int w, const int h, double focal, double focal_texture)
 4444:     {
 4445:         int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 4446:         int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 4447:     
 4448:         const int index  = j * h + i;          // (2d)  
 4449:         const int index1 = j * h * 3 + i * 3;  // (3d)
 4450:         const int t_max  = w * h;
 4451:         
 4452:         const float c1 = 2.0f / (float)h;
 4453:         const float c2 = 2.0f / (float)w;
 4454:         const float w2 = (float)w * 0.5f;
 4455:         const float h2 = (float)h * 0.5f;
 4456:         
 4457:         __syncthreads();            
 4458:         
 4459:         
 4460:         if (index> 0 && index < t_max){
 4461:                    
 4462:             float nx = j * c2 - 1.0f;
 4463:             float nx2 = nx * nx;
 4464:             
 4465:             float ny = i * c1 - 1.0f;
 4466:             float ny2 = ny * ny;
 4467:             float r = (float)sqrt(nx2 + ny2);
 4468:             if (0.0f <= r && r <= 1.0f){
 4469:                 float nr = (r * focal + 1.0f  - (float)sqrt(1.0f - (nx2 + ny2))) * focal_texture;
 4470:                 if (nr <= 1.0f){
 4471:                     float theta = (float)atan2(ny, nx);
 4472:                     float nxn = nr * (float)cos(theta);
 4473:                     float nyn = nr * (float)sin(theta);
 4474:                     int x2 = (int)(nxn * w2 + w2);
 4475:                     int y2 = (int)(nyn * h2 + h2);
 4476:                     int v  = (int)(y2 * w + x2);
 4477:                     int index2 = x2  * h * 3 + y2 * 3;
 4478:                     destination[index1 + 0] = source[index2 + 0];
 4479:                     destination[index1 + 1] = source[index2 + 1];
 4480:                     destination[index1 + 2] = source[index2 + 2];
 4481:                 }
 4482:             }            
 4483:         }
 4484:         __syncthreads();
 4485:     }
 4486:     ''',

 4563:     r'''
 4564: 
 4565:     extern "C" __global__
 4566: 
 4567:     void swirl_kernel(unsigned char * destination, unsigned char * source, double rad,   
 4568:     const int w, const int h, double x, double y)
 4569:     {
 4570:         int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 4571:         int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 4572: 
 4573:         const int index  = j * h + i;          // (2d)  
 4574:         const int index1 = j * h * 3 + i * 3;  // (3d)
 4575:         const int t_max  = w * h;
 4576: 
 4577: 
 4578:         __syncthreads();            
 4579: 
 4580:         if (index> 0 && index < t_max){   
 4581:             
 4582:             // 3 constant can be passed instead  
 4583:             float columns = x * w;
 4584:             float rows    = y * h;
 4585:             float r_max   = (float)sqrt(columns * columns + rows * rows);
 4586: 
 4587:             float di = (float)j - columns;
 4588:             float dj = (float)i - rows;
 4589: 
 4590:             float r = (float)sqrt(di * di + dj * dj);
 4591: 
 4592:             float c1 = (float)cos(rad * r/r_max);
 4593:             float c2 = (float)sin(rad * r/r_max);
 4594: 
 4595:             int diffx = (int)(di * c1 - dj * c2 + columns);
 4596:             int diffy = (int)(di * c2 + dj * c1 + rows);
 4597: 
 4598:             if ((diffx >-1 && diffx < w) && (diffy >-1 && diffy < h)){
 4599: 
 4600:                 int index2 = diffx * h * 3 + diffy * 3;
 4601:                 __syncthreads();
 4602:                 destination[index1 + 0] = source[index2 + 0];
 4603:                 destination[index1 + 1] = source[index2 + 1];
 4604:                 destination[index1 + 2] = source[index2 + 2];
 4605:             }       
 4606:         }
 4607:         __syncthreads();
 4608:     }
 4609:     ''',
 4610:     'swirl_kernel'
 4611: )

 4689:     void wave_kernel(unsigned char * destination, unsigned char * source, 
 4690:         double rad, int size, const int w, const int h)
 4691: {
 4692:     
 4693:     unsigned int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 4694:     unsigned int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 4695: 
 4696:     const int index1 = j * h * 3 + i * 3; 
 4697:     const int t_max1 = w * h * 3;
 4698:     
 4699:     const float c1 = 1.0f / (float)(size * size);
 4700:     
 4701:     if (i < h && j < w) {
 4702:     
 4703:         unsigned int y_pos = (unsigned int) (j + size + (int) ((float) sin(rad + (float) j * c1) * (float) size));
 4704:         unsigned int x_pos = (unsigned int) (i + size + (int) ((float) sin(rad + (float) i * c1) * (float) size));
 4705:      
 4706:         // % t_max1 help wrap around the image when index is overflow in the texture 
 4707:         unsigned int index2 = (unsigned int) (y_pos * h * 3 + x_pos * 3) % t_max1;

 4710:         destination[index1 + 1] = source[index2 + 1];
 4711:         destination[index1 + 2] = source[index2 + 2];

 4819:         const int w, const int h, int delta_x, int delta_y, double zoom, double fx)
 4820: {
 4821: 
 4822:     unsigned int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 4823:     unsigned int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 4824: 
 4825:     int index1 = j * h * 3 + i * 3;   
 4826:     const unsigned int t_max = w * h * 3;
 4827:     unsigned char local_memory[3]; 
 4828:     const float dw = (float)delta_x/(float)w;
 4829:     const float dh = (float)delta_y/(float)h;
 4830:     
 4831:     float nx = float((float)i / (float)h) - dh;  
 4832:     float ny = float((float)j / (float)w) - dw;
 4833:     
 4834:     float theta_rad = (float)atan2 (ny,nx);
 4835:         
 4836:     float nx2 = nx * nx;
 4837:     float ny2 = ny * ny; 
 4838:     
 4839:     float dist = (float)sqrt(nx2 + ny2); 
 4840:     
 4841:     float new_dist = dist * (zoom - fx);
 4842:     
 4843:     float new_ii = (float)cos((float)theta_rad) * new_dist ;
 4844:     float new_jj = (float)sin((float)theta_rad) * new_dist;
 4845:     
 4846:     int new_j = (int)((new_jj + dw) * (float)w); 
 4847:     int new_i = (int)((new_ii + dh) * (float)h); 
 4848:         
 4849:     if (i < h && j < w ) {
 4850:         __syncthreads();
 4851:         const int r = new_j * h * 3 + new_i * 3 + 0;      
 4852:         local_memory[0] = source[r];   
 4853:         destination[index1 + 0] = local_memory[0];
 4854: 
 4855:     }
 4856:     new_dist = dist * (zoom  - fx * 2); 
 4857:

 4859:     new_i = (int)(((float)cos((float)theta_rad) * new_dist + dh) * (float)h); 
 4860:         
 4861:     if (i < h && j < w ) {

 4866: 
 4867:     }
 4868:

 5096:     extern "C"

 5098:     __global__  void zoom_kernel(unsigned char * destination, unsigned char * source,
 5099:         const int w, const int h, int delta_x, int delta_y, double zoom)
 5100: {
 5101: 
 5102:     unsigned int i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
 5103:     unsigned int j = blockIdx.y * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
 5104: 
 5105:     int index1 = j * h * 3 + i * 3;   
 5106:     const unsigned int t_max = w * h * 3;  
 5107:     unsigned char local_memory[3]; 
 5108:     const float dw = float(delta_x)/(float)w;
 5109:     const float dh = (float)delta_y/(float)h;
 5110:     
 5111:     float nx = float((float)i / (float)h) - dh;  
 5112:     float ny = float((float)j / (float)w) - dw;
 5113:     
 5114:     float theta = (float)atan2 (ny,nx);
 5115:         
 5116:     float nx2 = nx * nx;
 5117:     float ny2 = ny * ny; 
 5118:     
 5119:     float dist = (float)sqrt(nx2 + ny2); 
 5120:     float new_dist = dist * zoom;
 5121:     
 5122:     int new_j = (int)(((float)sin((float)theta) * new_dist + dw) * (float)w); 
 5123:     int new_i = (int)(((float)cos((float)theta) * new_dist + dh) * (float)h); 
 5124:         
 5125:     if (i < h && j < w) {
 5126: 
 5127:         const int r = new_j * h * 3 + new_i * 3 + 0; 
 5128:         const int g = new_j * h * 3 + new_i * 3 + 1;
 5129:         const int b = new_j * h * 3 + new_i * 3 + 2;
 5130:         
 5131:         local_memory[0] = source[r];
 5132:         local_memory[1] = source[g];
 5133:         local_memory[2] = source[b];
 5134:         __syncthreads();
 5135:         destination[index1 + 0] = local_memory[0];
 5136:         destination[index1 + 1] = local_memory[1];
 5137:         destination[index1 + 2] = local_memory[2]; 
 5138:     }
 5139:      
 5140: 
 5141: }
